.TH "ib_map_mr_sg_pi" 9 "ib_map_mr_sg_pi" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
ib_map_mr_sg_pi \- Map the dma mapped SG lists for PI (protection information) and set an appropriate memory region for registration.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" ib_map_mr_sg_pi
.BI "(struct ib_mr *mr "  ","
.BI "struct scatterlist *data_sg "  ","
.BI "int data_sg_nents "  ","
.BI "unsigned int *data_sg_offset "  ","
.BI "struct scatterlist *meta_sg "  ","
.BI "int meta_sg_nents "  ","
.BI "unsigned int *meta_sg_offset "  ","
.BI "unsigned int page_size "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "mr" 12
memory region
.IP "data_sg" 12
dma mapped scatterlist for data
.IP "data_sg_nents" 12
number of entries in data_sg
.IP "data_sg_offset" 12
offset in bytes into data_sg
.IP "meta_sg" 12
dma mapped scatterlist for metadata
.IP "meta_sg_nents" 12
number of entries in meta_sg
.IP "meta_sg_offset" 12
offset in bytes into meta_sg
.IP "page_size" 12
page vector desired page size
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Constraints:
- The MR must be allocated with type IB_MR_TYPE_INTEGRITY.

After this completes successfully, the  memory region
is ready for registration.
.SH "RETURN"
0 on success.
